<tr><td bgcolor="#3F403F" width="98%" class="cheader"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><input type="hidden" name="PHPSESSID" value="...328fedb22570524062aeb1303" /><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/vs/articles/index.php3'>Marvel VS</option><option value='/heroclix/articles/articles.php'>HeroClix</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/articles/articles.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/articles/articles.php'>Ophidian 2350</option><option value='/magic/treports/treports.php'>The Wastelands</option></select></td></form></tr></table></td><td bgcolor="3F403F" valign="top" align="right" width="22"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/topcorner.gif" width="23" height="22" border="0" vspace="0" hspace="0" align="right"></td></tr>
<tr><td width="98%" colspan=2><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5" class="cbody">
<tr><td><font class="h1font"> Luke Skywalker, Rebel Scout<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(5.00)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/starwarsccg/main/mpage.php?member=175'>Scott "CRingwell" Lingrell</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/starwarsccg/main/mpage.php?member=175&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> April 20, 2005</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> Brandon Schele writes an article about the new Virtual Card from V9.<br />
<br />
Luke Skywalker, Rebel Scout <br />
Power 6 Ability 6 Deploy 7 Forfiet 8 [P][W] <br />
[P2] Deploys free to Endor. Adds 1 to his <br />
weapon destiny draws. At same location, <br />
opponent must first use 2 Force to fire a <br />
weapon. While Luke alone at an Endor site, <br />
Imperials on Endor must move (for free) towards <br />
Luke’s site (if possible). Immune to attrition < 6. <br />
<br />
Well there you are, the newest Luke. Quite a lot to take in at first, I know. There are a lot of things this guy can do, and I&#39;ll break it all down for you. His uses are quite varied, but he&#39;s obviously made to be used primarily on Endor. With this set being based on Endor, he gives a big help to decks like RST and TIGIH, and can also be utilized very effectively in a Careful Planning(V) deck on Endor and possibly other LS decks provided you don&#39;t mind the 7 deploy cost or you play the Endor Docking Bay. Anyway, onto the breakdown of the card. <br />
<br />
The stats for the card are fairly standard for a Jedi Luke, with the only thing being a bit high is Luke&#39;s deploy of 7. This of course is reduced to free when he&#39;s deployed to Endor, which makes sense given what his intent is. I&#39;m sure this was to deter people from using him in every LS deck, therefore introducing somewhat of a balancing factor. His immunity to < 6 is also on par with Lord Vader, which is a good thing. <br />
<br />
Adds 1 to his weapon destiny draws. At same location, opponent must first use 2 Force to fire a weapon. The first line of this text was to match Lord Vader&#39;s ability to add to his lightsaber destiny draws, and allows him to hit the different dark jedi much easier. Causing the opponent to pay 2 force to fire a weapon at same location is a very strong line, and most likely the best line on the card. This forces Maul with Double Bladed Lightsaber to pay 4 force if he wants to swing twice, and it forces the opponent to either choose to deploy that extra character or save the force to fire their weapons. This will help keep your mains alive on Endor, especially in a deck like Rebel Strike Team where your guys generally have a tough time sticking around against Maul, Vader, and other strong DS characters. <br />
<br />
While Luke alone at an Endor site, Imperials on Endor must move (for free) towards Luke’s site (if possible). Now this is the most unique line on Luke, and a very good one as well. I know the uses for this aren&#39;t completely obvious right away, but that&#39;s probably why I&#39;m here to explain them to you. The first use for this is in There Is Good In Him. If you start Luke Skywalker, Rebel Scout(V) with the objective, you gain one distinct advantage: You take away the Dark Side&#39;s ability to force choke you by putting an Imperial at the Endor: Docking Bay by using Luke&#39;s text to force them to move the Imperial towards Luke. In most games, this would cause Luke to be captured first turn, which means their Imperial will be at a non-battleground. This allows you to still activate from Chief Chirpa&#39;s Hut, rather than limiting you to usually only 2 activation on your first turn. The only exceptions to this is if Emperor is deployed(and due to his gametext is unable to move towards Luke), or if there is an Endor site between the docking bay and the hut. In the second case, you&#39;d still get the bonus generation from Luke&#39;s site due to there being no Imperial at the docking bay. Finally, the dark side can get around this in ONE way: deploying to a different docking bay, and then transiting to the Endor: Docking Bay using their regular move. <br />
<br />
The other use for this a far less obvious one, but it&#39;s in Rebel Strike Team. If you deploy Luke away from the Bunker, and there are Imperials in the Bunker, you force them to move out of the Bunker and towards Luke, possibly giving you a chance to blow the Bunker away. There&#39;s another card in the set that helps this portion of his text, but obviously I can&#39;t reveal that card YET. <br />
<br />
So there you have it, a light side main spoiled, and a fairly strong one at that. He obviously has his uses, and will definitely see play in Endor based Light Side decks, but won&#39;t be the obvious choice over Luke Skywalker, Jedi Knight due to his much lower destiny number. And now, for a sample deck using him(and of course Mon Mothma): <br />
<br />
Thrown Back(V) <br />
Rebel Strike Team/Garrison Destroyed <br />
Endor <br />
Endor: Rebel Landing Site <br />
Heading For The Medical Frigate <br />
Strike Planning <br />
The Shield Is Down <br />
Sai&#39;Tor Kal&#39;Fas(V) <br />
<br />
Endor: Back Door <br />
Endor: Dense Forest <br />
Deactivate The Shield Generator <br />
<br />
Mon Mothma(V) <br />
Luke Skywalker, Rebel Scout(V) x3 <br />
Princess Leia(V) x2 <br />
General Solo <br />
General Crix Madine <br />
Corporal Kensaric <br />
Corporal Midge <br />
Lieutenant Blount <br />
Chewbacca Of Kashyyyk <br />
Obi-Wan Kenobi(V) x2 <br />
Qui-Gon Jinn With Lightsaber x2 <br />
Corran Horn x2 <br />
Lando Calrissian, Scoundrel <br />
<br />
Luke&#39;s Lightsaber x2 <br />
Leia&#39;s Blaster Rifle <br />
Obi Wan&#39;s Lightsaber <br />
Explosive Charge x2 <br />
<br />
Tantive 4(V) x2 <br />
Bright Hope(V) x2 <br />
Spiral <br />
<br />
Honor Of The Jedi <br />
Flash Of Insight(V) x2 <br />
Civil Disorder(V) <br />
Mantellian Savrip <br />
<br />
Throw Me Another Charge x3 <br />
Blaster Deflection x2 <br />
Sorry About The Mess & Blaster Proficiency <br />
Escape Pod(V) x2 <br />
Grimtaash <br />
Houjix <br />
Control & Tunnel Vision x2 <br />
Hear Me Baby, Hold Together x2 <br />
<br />
This is a fairly standard RST deck with immunity mains to TRY to get staying power. Nothing really special about it, just deploy your stuff and hope you can blow the bunker. Mon Mothma(V) pulls your extra battleground, Crix pulls a couple of different guys, and the rest of the guys are your big guys that can hopefully help eliminate characters and stay around long enough to help win the game. <br />
<br />
Space is fairly minimal, just enough to disrupt the opponent and possibly set up a big drain with Tantive 4(V) and one of your pilots, with Bright Hope(V) hopefully there to support it. Hear Me Baby, Hold Together is once against anti-cannon to help keep your ships from being shot down. <br />
<br />
<br />
Brandon Schele <br />
2004 SW:CCG World Champion <br />
2005 Corellia Regionals Winner<br />
